'''Hayim de lah Rozah'''<ref name=Th>{{cite book|year=1848|title=Torat Hakham|script-title=he:תורת חכם|url=http://hebrewbooks.org/7547|language=he|location=Thessaloniki|oclc=233312345|access-date=Oct 28, 2016}}</ref> (also spelled''' Chaim Delharoza'''<ref name=ami>{{cite magazine|last=Horovitz|first=Isaac|date=Dec 9, 2015|title=The Cave and the King|url=|magazine=[[Ami (magazine)|Ami]]|issue=246|pages=111–120}}</ref>) was a Spanish [[rabbi]] and [[kabbalist]].<ref name=ami/>
After the [[Spanish expulsion]], he wandered until he reached [[Jerusalem]] where he joined the ''[[chavurah]]'' of Rabbi [[Shalom Sharabi]], becoming a scholar of the [[Beit El Synagogue]] and a close disciple and friend of Rabbi Sharabi.<ref name=ami/>
Rabbi de lah Rozah authored the ''[[Sefer (Hebrew)|sefer]] Torat Hakham''.<ref name=Th/><ref name=ami/>
