The '''Indonesia Dharma Awakening Party''' (''Partai Kebangkitan Dharma Indonesia'') is a [[Hindu]] political party that has announced it will contest the [[Indonesian presidential election, 2009|Indonesia's 2009 elections]].

==Platform==
Party chairman Ngurah Arya has stated the platform will be {{cquote|an open party that strengthens the nationalistic, democratic, humanist and pluralistic attitudes based on principles of religion, morality and truth.<ref name="jp">[http://www.thejakartapost.com/yesterdaydetail.asp?fileid=20071224.H04 New Hindu party expects to run in 2009 elections]{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Jakarta Post - December 24, 2007</ref>}}

==Goals==
The party has four goals:
# Reconciliation
# Reform
# Reconstructing Indonesia's Morality
# Recovering Indonesia's Status as a Religious nation<ref name="jp" />

