{{Use British English|date=October 2017}}[[File:Eziden und andere Minderheiten in Ninive (Gastvortrag), (016) Grußwort von Bernd Strauch, 1. Bürgermeister und Vertreter des Oberbürgermeisters von Hannover.jpg|thumb|300px|Hannover's mayor [[Bernd Strauch]] welcoming [[Atheel al-Nujaifi]], governor of [[Nineveh Governorate|Nineveh]], at the ''Ezidische Akademie'' in 2014]]
The '''Yazidi Academy''' ({{lang-de|Jesidische Akademie}}) is a [[non-profit organisation]] and [[learned society]] based in [[Hanover]], [[Germany]].
The organisation was founded in 2009, it concerns itself with the historical and current situation of the [[Yazidis]]. Since then, it has also published the [[German-language]] [[magazine]] ''Zeitschrift der Ezidischen Akademie. Forum für Diskussionsbeiträge zum Ezidentum''.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=Ezidische Akademie |title=About us |url=http://www.ezidische-akademie.de/en/about-us.html |accessdate=4 November 2015}}</ref> It also hosts the Yazidi Library that had been established in 2007.
The Yazidi Academy is a member of the network of migrants initiatives ''MiSO''.<ref>[http://www.misonetz.de/index.php?article_id=45 MiSO-Mitglieder stellen sich vor: Ezidische Akademie e. V.], MiSO-Netzwerk Hannover</ref> It offers [[Learning to read|literacy]] and [[German language|German]] courses as well as legal counselling for [[asylum seekers]].<ref>[http://www.ezidische-akademie.de/de/asylhilfe-niedersachsen.html Asylhilfe Niedersachsen], ezidische-akademie.de</ref>
